This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of a basic operator in data management systems, the set containment join. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the join in SQL queries and data mining algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new methodology for reducing the space and time cost of the join, which could be relevant to the distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
